Environment

Require:

- Arduino IDE : apt-get install arduino

1. Download Openmolo Libraries:

svn co svn://svn.backupnet.com.ar/OpenMolo/trunk

2. Download UIPEthernet

$ git clone https://github.com/ntruchsess/arduino_uip UIPEthernet
$ cd [path to Arduino distribution]/libraries

* Ubuntu path
$ cd /usr/share/arduino/libraries/

3. Bind Openmolo & UIPEthernet libraries with arduino

$ cd [path to Arduino distribution]/libraries

*Ubuntu path
$ cd /usr/share/arduino/libraries/

sudo ln -s /home/ggoral/src/arduino/trunk/Librerias/CMEA/
sudo ln -s /home/ggoral/src/arduino/trunk/Librerias/Time
sudo ln -s /home/ggoral/src/arduino/trunk/Librerias/Entradas
sudo ln -s /home/ggoral/src/arduino/trunk/Librerias/Salidas
sudo ln -s /home/ggoral/src/arduino/trunk/Librerias/Cron
sudo ln -s /home/ggoral/src/arduino/trunk/Librerias/UIPEthernet

3. Install
i. open arduino
$ arduino

ii. open file Prueba_Socket.pde
file -> open -> arol/arduino/Prueba_Socket/Prueba_Socket.pde

iii. Verify & Upload

